runs.comm: from round the stumps, on the pads, nudged behind square-leg
floated full around off stump line, lifted over to the right of long-on
Whack! Another flighted delivery and he goes down on his knee to slog sweep it for a four
turns in slowly from the middle and leg line, and hits the pad
stays back to dab it to point for a single
moves outside leg and tries to drive against the spin, through extra cover, but edges it to the on side
full in length and well outside off stump, left alone
gets forward for the big shot but mistimes it completely .. ends up flat batting it weakly back to Bond
tries to shuffle across and work it to the on side but misses it completely. The ball cuts in to kiss the front pad enroute to the keeper who dives forward to 'catch' it and appeals. Not out.
cuts in from a length, towards the middle stump line, dabbed away past square-leg for a single
way way outside the off stump. Wide.
slower one, short in length outside off, Taibu is through early with the cut shot and the ball goes under the bat
Fabulicious! Full pitched around the off stump line and Taibu plays a scorching square drive through cover point.
moves down the track and pushes it to left of mid-on for a single
shuffles to the off side, tries to swing it to the on side, misses and it rolls off the pad
moves outside leg stump and can't reach the ball outside off stump
gets outside leg, the bowler follows him with a length delivery, bunted past square-leg
gets outside leg, Southee follows him with a length delivery and Taibu stays adjacent to the line and cuts it from outside leg to third man
Wild swing and a miss. A typical Twenty20 charge and a miss.
gets forward to swat it to mid-on for a quick single ..
Awww. What a hit. He moved outside leg stump initially before he went down on his knee to reach the full delivery outside off and whiplashed it over backward point!
Very skilful. It was a delivery that bounced outside off, a slow leg cutter, Taibu adjusted to upper cut it over first slip. Third man gets across to cut it off
high bouncer .. it wouldn't have been too far away from being called a wide
slower one outside off, Taibu walks across and swats it wide of mid-on for a single
moves outside leg and pushes the length delivery to cover
More innovation from Taibu. He moved well back inside the crease, cleared the front foot to swing the full delivery to backward square-leg boundary. He adjusted superbly the line and the length
cuts this one wide of deep backward point
slower one, Taibu is late in picking it but adjusts to almost scoop it over midwicket.
The slow bouncer does the trick. Taibu waited and crashed a pull shot but found the fielder at square-leg. Oh well. Breezy. Entertaining. But it's over now.
short in length on the middle and leg, the left-handed Blignaut shovels it past square-leg
The keeper was standing up and instead of moving down the track, he backed away to the leg side and thrashed this full delivery over covers. Thwack!
leans forward to flick it past square-leg
gets outside leg and goes for yet another big off drive but edges it to his pad
leans forward to drag this full length delivery to deep square-leg region
Flamboyant whack. He picked the slow off cutter and crashed it from the leg stump line to the cover boundary. He took the aerial route

shout for run out Blignaut stabbed it in front of him but he didn't know where the ball went. He turned back, turned front before he head the call from the non-striker and dashed across. the bowler rushed forward, picked, turned and hit the stumps at the non-striker's end but Blignaut was just in
walked to the off side, Oram pushed the ball wider outside off and Masakadza throws his hand at it and the ball flies wide of the keeper
fuller and straighter, pushed down to mid-on for a single
steps out and works the ball to deep midwicket region
from round the stumps, slips it on the leg stump line
lands around off and turns away, Andy goes for the big slog sweep but doesn't connect
on the middle stump line, turns and jumps, stabbed away to point

Masakadza is run out. It was slog swept to deep square-leg and Oram moved to his left and released the throw quickly. It wasn't accurate but the keeper reached out, collected it and broke the stumps. Masakadza tried to dive in but ...
leans forward to drive it for a single
Shout for lbw. It turned in from outside leg, moved past the attempted slog sweep and hit him.
on the off stump line, on a length, driven to sweeper cover

Clatter! Blignaut, who showed an immense liking for the slog sweep today, is bowled, going for yet another slog sweep. The ball went past the big heave to fall on the stumps. It landed around leg, turned down leg side, caught the glove and went in to hit the stumps
leans forward to defend to the off side
turned away to square-leg for a single
slows up the pace, loops it outside off, dabbed to point
turns in from middle and leg and bounds off the pad
Caught at long-on. He went for the big shot but couldn't clear the man in the deep. Three quick wickets threaten to peg back Zimbabwe. Chigumbura, who starred in the warm-up games, is gone.
turns in slowly from outside off stump, dabbed to the off side

Five down and struggling. What a quick turn around. It was a slow loopy off break, Nathan has been constantly slowing up the pace, and the batsman lunged forward as he was beaten in flight and ended up tamely scooping it back to the bowler
It was turned to the on side and they rush across for a quick single... Risky..
drifts across from round the stumps and the ball turns in to hit the pad

Bogo Jonito! Nathan slowed it up nicely, it drifted in the air from round the stumps, drew the batsman out of his crease before it dipped and turned away past the lunge. Stumped! Ervine was not looking for the big shot, he was just fataly attracted by the flight and leaned forward to turn it to the on side for a single
gets forward to push it away for a single
gets forward to nudge it to the on side
on the off stump line, pushed away to the off side
turns from middle and off, pushed back to the bowler
stays back to cut it to sweeper cover
leans forward to defend to the fof side
turns in from outside off, gets forward to push it away
leans forward to turn it past square-leg
leans forward to dab the off break to the on side
leans forward to off drive it to long-off
fetches it from outside off and sweeps it for a single
another sweep. Another single
slows up the pace even further, tosses it up, flicked away for a single
quicker, moves in towards middle, pushed out back to Dan
lovely delivery. He slowed up the pace and got it to dip on the batsman who had charged out but adjusted to push it to covers
full in length on the middle stump line, pushed out to the on side
around the off stump line, chopped to third man
Seven down and what a staggering turn around.  This time it was Maruma who charged down the track and went for the lofted six but holed out at long-on
gets forward to push it away to the off side
Gone! Clatter! Mucherly fun if you are an Kiwi fan. It cuts in from outside off stump, the bat was pushed outside the line, the ball collided with the inside edge and fell on the stumps
Plumb! Another in cutter, another wicket. It darted in from just outside off, Utseya played around it and was hit in front. As Fred Trueman would have said, "What's going off out there?!"
full and well outside off stump, goes for the drive but can't connect
the slow bouncer well outside off. Wide
kicks up from short of length, pushed away to point
banged in short, pulled away to deep square-leg region for couple of runs
slower one, full in length, turned wide of midwicket
length delivery outside off, pushed to left of Vettori at mid-off
banged in short, pulled weakly but will get a single
He won't get his hattrick. It was a length delivery on the off and middle line, defended on the front foot
around the off stump, steered to backward point
cuts in towards the leg stump, the batsman stays adjacent to the line and almost chops it wide of backward point
full in length, straight, pushed towards long-on for a single
short in length on the middle and off, nudged past square-leg
Almost cleaned up by the nip backer. It cut in from just outside off, moved past the lame poke and missed the off stump,. The keeper, standing up to the stumps, doesn't collect cleanly
The big slog sweep was attempted but he missed it completely. No wood on leather but there was leather on the wood. Clatter!
